{"parse":{"title":"Otto Scharmer","pageid":29825803,"revid":859559005,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox biography vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\"><span class=\"fn\">Otto Scharmer</span></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Otto_Scharmer.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Otto Scharmer.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2f/Otto_Scharmer.jpg/220px-Otto_Scharmer.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"330\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2f/Otto_Scharmer.jpg/330px-Otto_Scharmer.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2f/Otto_Scharmer.jpg/440px-Otto_Scharmer.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2592\" data-file-height=\"3888\" /></a><div>Otto Scharmer</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n1961 (age&#160;56&#8211;57)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Citizenship</th><td class=\"category\">\nGermany</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alma&#160;mater</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Witten/Herdecke_University\" title=\"Witten/Herdecke University\">Witten/Herdecke University</a></li></ul>\n</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Known&#160;for</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Theory_U\" title=\"Theory U\">Theory U</a></li></ul>\n</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Website</th><td>\nwww.ottoscharmer.com</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Claus Otto Scharmer</b> (born 1961) is a Senior Lecturer at <a href=\"/wiki/Massachusetts_Institute_of_Technology\" title=\"Massachusetts Institute of Technology\">Massachusetts Institute of Technology</a> (MIT),<sup id=\"cite_ref-MIT_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-MIT-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> a Thousand Talents Program Professor at <a href=\"/wiki/Tsinghua_University\" title=\"Tsinghua University\">Tsinghua University</a>, Beijing,<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> and co-founder of the Presencing Institute.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>  He chairs the <a href=\"/wiki/Traditions_and_student_activities_at_MIT#IDEAS_Global_Challenge\" title=\"Traditions and student activities at MIT\">MIT IDEAS</a> program for cross-sector innovation that aims to help \"stakeholders from business, government, civil society to innovate at the level of the whole system\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-MIT_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-MIT-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Scharmer is author of the change management method and book <i><a href=\"/wiki/Theory_U\" title=\"Theory U\">Theory U</a></i>, and he is co-author of the book <i>Leading from the Emerging Future</i> that outlines \"eight <a href=\"/wiki/Acupuncture_point\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Acupuncture point\">acupuncture points</a> for transforming capitalism\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> In 2015 he co-founded the <a href=\"/wiki/MITx\" title=\"MITx\">MITx</a> u.lab,<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> a <a href=\"/wiki/Massive_open_online_course\" title=\"Massive open online course\">massive open online course</a> for \"leading profound change\" in which more than 45,000 users from 185 countries have participated.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> With his colleagues he has delivered leadership development programs for corporate clients and co-facilitated innovation labs on reinventing education, health, business, government, and well-being.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (May 2017)\">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:172px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Theory_U_image.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/22/Theory_U_image.svg/170px-Theory_U_image.svg.png\" width=\"170\" height=\"132\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/22/Theory_U_image.svg/255px-Theory_U_image.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/22/Theory_U_image.svg/340px-Theory_U_image.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"555\" data-file-height=\"432\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Theory_U_image.svg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/wiki/Theory_U\" title=\"Theory U\">Theory U</a> diagram.</div></div></div>\n<p>Scharmer received the Jamieson Prize for Excellence in Teaching at MIT (2015),<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> and the EU Leonardo Corporate Learning Award for the contributions of Theory U to the future of management (2016).<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> In 2017 he was ranked #1 of the world's top 30 education professionals by globalgurus.org.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_publications\">Selected publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Otto_Scharmer&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Selected publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite id=\"CITEREFSengeScharmerJaworskyFlowers2004\" class=\"citation book\"><a href=\"/wiki/Peter_Senge\" title=\"Peter Senge\">Senge, Peter M.</a>; Scharmer, Claus Otto; Jaworsky, Joseph; <a href=\"/wiki/Betty_Sue_Flowers\" title=\"Betty Sue Flowers\">Flowers, Betty Sue</a> (2004). <i>Presence: exploring profound change in people, organizations, and society</i> (1st ed.). New York: <a href=\"/wiki/Doubleday_(publisher)\" title=\"Doubleday (publisher)\">Currency/Doubleday</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/038551624X\" title=\"Special:BookSources/038551624X\">038551624X</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/OCLC\" title=\"OCLC\">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.worldcat.org/oclc/61257585\">61257585</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Presence%3A+exploring+profound+change+in+people%2C+organizations%2C+and+society&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.edition=1st&amp;rft.pub=Currency%2FDoubleday&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F61257585&amp;rft.isbn=038551624X&amp;rft.aulast=Senge&amp;rft.aufirst=Peter+M.&amp;rft.au=Scharmer%2C+Claus+Otto&amp;rft.au=Jaworsky%2C+Joseph&amp;rft.au=Flowers%2C+Betty+Sue&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AOtto+Scharmer\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite id=\"CITEREFScharmer2016\" class=\"citation book\">Scharmer, Claus Otto (2016) [2007]. <i>Theory U: leading from the emerging future</i>. A BK business book (2nd ed.). San Francisco: Berrett-Koehler. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781626567986\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9781626567986\">9781626567986</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/OCLC\" title=\"OCLC\">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.worldcat.org/oclc/944179658\">944179658</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Theory+U%3A+leading+from+the+emerging+future&amp;rft.place=San+Francisco&amp;rft.series=A+BK+business+book&amp;rft.edition=2nd&amp;rft.pub=Berrett-Koehler&amp;rft.date=2016&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F944179658&amp;rft.isbn=9781626567986&amp;rft.aulast=Scharmer&amp;rft.aufirst=Claus+Otto&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AOtto+Scharmer\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite id=\"CITEREFScharmerK\u00e4ufer2013\" class=\"citation book\">Scharmer, Otto; K\u00e4ufer, Katrin (2013). <i>Leading from the emerging future: from ego-system to eco-system economies</i> (1st ed.). San Francisco: Berrett-Koehler. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781605099262\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9781605099262\">9781605099262</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/OCLC\" title=\"OCLC\">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.worldcat.org/oclc/813920439\">813920439</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Leading+from+the+emerging+future%3A+from+ego-system+to+eco-system+economies&amp;rft.place=San+Francisco&amp;rft.edition=1st&amp;rft.pub=Berrett-Koehler&amp;rft.date=2013&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F813920439&amp;rft.isbn=9781605099262&amp;rft.aulast=Scharmer&amp;rft.aufirst=Otto&amp;rft.au=K%C3%A4ufer%2C+Katrin&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AOtto+Scharmer\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Otto_Scharmer&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div clas